            {
                "type": "heading",
                "level": 2,
                "text": "Defining the Core Architecture: Blockchain and Distributed Ledgers"
            },
            {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "To understand why Web3 is considered a paradigm shift, one must first demystify blockchain technology. At its most fundamental level, a blockchain is a specific type of Distributed Ledger Technology (DLT). It functions as a shared, immutable database where information is recorded in a way that makes it virtually impossible to hack or manipulate. Unlike traditional databases, which are stored on a single server or managed by a centralized administrator, a blockchain distributes data across a global network of independent computers known as nodes."
            },
